    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-gray-100">
        <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
            <div class="text-center mb-12">
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">Common questions about smart home integration in Arlington residences.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md mb-4 overflow-hidden">
                    <div class="p-6">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-lg text-gray-800 mb-2">Can I integrate smart home technology in my Arlington high-rise condo?</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-700">Absolutely! Arlington's high-rise condominiums are excellent candidates for smart home technology. We specialize in solutions specifically designed for multi-unit buildings, including wireless systems that don't require extensive rewiring, devices that work well in smaller spaces, and setups that comply with HOA regulations. We can install smart lighting, thermostats, security systems, and entertainment controls that function perfectly in high-rise environments. For condos with concrete walls or signal challenges, we implement mesh networks and signal boosters to ensure seamless operation throughout your Arlington high-rise home.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md mb-4 overflow-hidden">
                    <div class="p-6">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-lg text-gray-800 mb-2">Which smart home system is best for my Arlington home?</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-700">The ideal smart home system depends on your specific needs, preferences, and existing technology. During our consultation, we assess factors unique to your Arlington residence, including home size, layout, construction type, internet infrastructure, and your lifestyle priorities. For many Arlington homeowners, we recommend platform-agnostic systems like Samsung SmartThings that work with multiple device brands and voice assistants. Tech-savvy users might prefer the customization of Home Assistant, while those prioritizing simplicity might benefit from ecosystems like Apple HomeKit. We'll help you select a system that balances functionality, user-friendliness, security, and future expandability based on your specific Arlington home environment.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md mb-4 overflow-hidden">
                    <div class="p-6">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-lg text-gray-800 mb-2">How disruptive is smart home installation in an Arlington residence?</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-700">We minimize disruption during smart home installations in Arlington homes. Many modern smart devices use wireless technology and can be installed with minimal impact on your living space. For lighting control, we often replace existing switches and fixtures without requiring additional wiring. For more comprehensive systems requiring new wiring, our experienced electricians use specialized techniques to run cables with minimal wall opening, particularly important in Arlington's older homes. We typically complete most installations in 1-3 days, depending on project scope, and we thoroughly clean up after each work session. We coordinate carefully with Arlington condo residents to ensure building requirements are met and neighbor disruption is minimized.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md mb-4 overflow-hidden">
                    <div class="p-6">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-lg text-gray-800 mb-2">Can I start with a few smart devices and expand later in my Arlington home?</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-700">This is a popular approach for many Arlington homeowners! We can design a phased implementation plan that starts with your highest-priority smart home elements while establishing a foundation for future expansion. We typically recommend beginning with core infrastructure like robust networking and a flexible smart home hub that can accommodate additional devices over time. Many Arlington residents start with smart lighting and thermostats for immediate energy savings and comfort benefits, then add security features, entertainment controls, and more advanced automation later. We'll help you create a roadmap that fits your budget while ensuring all current and future components will work together seamlessly in your Arlington home.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden">
                    <div class="p-6">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-lg text-gray-800 mb-2">How reliable is smart home technology in Arlington's urban environment?</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-700">Arlington's dense urban environment presents unique challenges for smart home reliability that we've developed specific solutions to address. In high-rise buildings and areas with significant wireless congestion, we implement enterprise-grade networking equipment with advanced features like band steering and multiple access points to ensure stable connections. For homes experiencing inconsistent internet service, we design systems with local control capabilities that continue functioning during outages. We select devices with proven reliability records and implement redundant systems for critical functions. Our installation process includes thorough signal testing throughout your Arlington home and strategic device placement to avoid interference. Additionally, we provide regular maintenance services to keep your system operating optimally and offer rapid response support if issues arise in your Arlington smart home.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

